Your Honor, 

I, David Lambert, stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of driving whilst disqualified. I deeply regret my actions and acknowledge the serious nature of my offense.

I must admit that I failed to consider the restrictions placed upon me by the court. It was careless and thoughtless of me to drive to the supermarket without realizing that I was prohibited from doing so. I take full responsibility for this lapse in judgment and I am truly embarrassed by my actions.

As a 55-year-old individual with no criminal record, I am genuinely remorseful for my actions and the impact they have had on the court's previous order. I apologize for not adhering to the court's directive and understand the consequences it carries.

If given the opportunity, I am willing to undertake any necessary courses or programs that may be required, in order to better educate myself and address any underlying issues that have contributed to my actions.

In conclusion, I stand before you today, fully acknowledging my guilt and accepting the consequences that come with it. I humbly ask for your guidance and leniency as I strive to make amends and prevent any repetition of such behavior.

Thank you, Your Honor.

